I personally feel my college gives a wode range of opportunities to each and everyone who want to achieve something in their feild of intrest whatever it may be academics of extra ciricullar activities  Fee Structure And Facilities  The only drawback I feel about the college is fee structure. The fee is quite large amount. A student need to pay around 3.2 lakhs of tution fee and a fee of 80 thousand for hostel and food if one is doesn't get any scholarship and this structure keep changing.  Placement Wing  10/10  Placement scenario is also very good.Being one of the tier-A college in India the average package ranges between 14 lakhs and 16 lakhs.The highest package usually crosses one crore and most probably there will be 100% placements  Hostel Facilities  10/10  I currently live in a hostel. I'm a sophomore and I could opt for a single occupancy room or a double occupancy. I've opted for a double occupancy room.It has a very good infrastructure. They give you a cot a table a chair a white board etc.  Alumni  My college has extra ordinary alumni network. Alumni are very helping and are always constantly helping to take the college forward. Alumni meets/reunion take place very frequently and they guide you about the life outside and after bits.  Faculty  10/10  The faculty is very good.Everyone has completed their Ph.D and are very passionate about teaching. Our college is one of the best colleges for faculty in India if you want to carry forward your reasearch work.  Campus Life  10/10  My college has a very good infrastructure and advanced sports facilities and laboratories. We get a lot of free time to develope our skills in a sport that we used to play or even their are handfull of opportunities to learn a new sport/music instrument etc.  Course Curriculum Overview  10/10  The course curriculum is very flexible and you have a freedom to make your own timetable and opt for the courses of your choice which no other college in India provides.But there are a lot of exams that you have to write and the institute is very keen about transparency of exams.  College Events  10/10  There are many events that occur in my college. There are three fests we celebrate every year.they are BOSM(sports fest) OASIS(cultural fest) APOGEE(technical fest).Among the three oasis being the second largest cultual fest is celebrated on a high scale.Apart from these there are many events that go through out the year  Loan/ Scholarship Provisions  My college gives scholarships on two criteria.The first one is Merit and the other one is Merit cum need scholarship. Out of the two if you need to avail the first one there is CGPA cutoff of about 9.7 and to avail the second one there is a CGPA cutoff of 6.1 and annual income cutoff of 10 LPA.

The Birla Institute of Technology & Science, BITS Pilani is an all-India Institute for higher education. The primary motive of BITS is to "train young men and women able and eager to create and put into action such ideas, methods, techniques and information". The Institute is a dream come true of its founder late Mr G.D.Birla - an eminent industrialist, a participant in Indian freedom struggle and a close associate of the Father of Indian Nation late Mr. Mohandas Karamchand Gandhi (Mahatma Gandhi). What started in early 1900s as a small school, blossomed into a set of colleges for higher education, ranging from the Humanities to Engineering until 1964 when all these colleges amalgamated to culminate into a unique Indian University of International standing. This university was christened as the Birla Institute of Technology and Science, Pilani, known to many as BITS, Pilani.  Over the years, BITS has provided the highest quality technical education to students from all over India admitted on the basis of merit. Its graduates may be found throughout the world in all areas of engineering, science and commerce. BITS symbolizes the maturing of Indian technical ability and "can-do" entrepreneurial spirit, especially as derived from the private sector. BITS is located in the Vidya Vihar campus adjacent to the town of Pilani in Rajasthan.

Placements : The placements are very good if you have a 'bitsian' tag name. The average salary offered for CS being around 17 LPA (Oracle, Flipkart and Amazon). For ECE and EEE, the package offered is around 12 LPA. About 95% of the students were placed in the core placements, which is also pretty good with companies like Qualcomm, Intel, Schlumberger and Shell. The average package offered was around 10 LPA.The median package offered is around 14-15 LPA. The placements are average for ET/MF department. You have to score a decent CGPA and have a couple of projects to get placed in the tier 1 companies. The placements for other departments like finance and analytics are improving. The civil and chemical have not such impressive placements, but if you're good, then you will get placed. The students of remaining branches tend to sit for the sectors mentioned above, but if you have an impressive resume, BITS-H can make you get placed from any branch.  Infrastructure : Bits Pilani, Hyderabad campus, has great infrastructure. Especially, the auditorium, which is one of the biggest and best in Asia is present here. It also has on of the best libraries in India, which can house around 1000 students. All research labs are well-equipped, and hostel rooms are well maintained.  Faculty : The faculty are good but not great. You need to rely on self-learning. The course curriculum is pretty flexible, as students are given a lot of choice in choosing electives and humanities subject. However, the competition is pretty high, and grading is a bit harsh for core subjects.  Other : Bits, Hyderabad has the biggest fest in South India, known as 'pearl'. People like Farhan Akhtar visited the campus. The campus surrounding is beautiful with the forest. There are good sports departments.
